properties.name: Stirling Drive
properties.description: "Named after the castle at Stirling, the County town of Stirlingshire, Scotland" (Mathew, 2008, p. 115).
properties.refs: Mathew, J. (2008). Highways and Byways: The Origin of Townsville Street Names (Revised ed.). Townsville, QLD: Townsville Library Service.

properties.name: Cottesmore Crescent
properties.description: "A village of Rutland County, England, which gives its name to a famous hunt. It has a long connection with the Earls of Lonsdale" (Mathew, 2008, p. 36).
properties.refs: Mathew, J. (2008). Highways and Byways: The Origin of Townsville Street Names (Revised ed.). Townsville, QLD: Townsville Library Service.

properties.name: Hampton Court
properties.description: "Named after a palace at Hampton, near London, built by Cardinal Wolsey and enlarged by Henry VIII" (Mathew, 2008, p. 58).
properties.refs: Mathew, J. (2008). Highways and Byways: The Origin of Townsville Street Names (Revised ed.). Townsville, QLD: Townsville Library Service.

properties.name: Arundel Court
properties.description: "Named after a palace at Hampton, near London, built by Cardinal Wolsey and enlarged by Henry VIII" (Mathew, 2008, p. 11).
properties.refs: Mathew, J. (2008). Highways and Byways: The Origin of Townsville Street Names (Revised ed.). Townsville, QLD: Townsville Library Service.

properties.name: Durham Court
properties.description: "Named after Durham Castle which, although now part of Durham University, was once the residence of the prince bishops of Durham." (Mathew, 2008, p. 43).
properties.refs: Mathew, J. (2008). Highways and Byways: The Origin of Townsville Street Names (Revised ed.). Townsville, QLD: Townsville Library Service.
